---
import LegalPage from "../components/LegalPage.astro";
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy - VivyShot"
  description="Privacy Policy for VivyShot, an open source screenshot capture and recording app by Vivy Technologies Co., Limited."
  canonicalPath="/privacy"
  ogType="article"
>
  <LegalPage title="Privacy Policy" lastUpdated="April 5, 2026">
    <section>
      <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
      <p>
        Vivy Technologies Co., Limited ("we", "our", or "us") operates VivyShot. This Privacy Policy
        explains how we handle information related to the website, support requests, and official app
        distributions.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>2. Website Information</h2>
      <p>
        The VivyShot website is primarily informational. We do not claim cloud account features,
        synchronized user storage, or hosted project services unless those features are explicitly
        released and documented.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>3. App Data</h2>
      <p>
        VivyShot is intended to perform screenshot capture, editing, and export workflows primarily on
        your device. Depending on the release, the app may store projects, annotations, and export
        settings locally on your Mac.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>4. Support Requests</h2>
      <p>
        If you contact support, we receive the information you send us, such as your email address,
        device details, screenshots, logs, and reproduction notes. We use that information only to
        respond to your request and improve the product.
      </p>
      <p>
        Crash reports are submitted only when you choose to send them, and may be opened as a public
        GitHub issue with the crash details you review before submission.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>5. Purchases</h2>
      <p>
        If official VivyShot binaries are distributed through Apple’s App Store, billing is handled by
        Apple. We do not receive your full payment details.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>6. How We Use Information</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>To provide and maintain the website and app</li>
        <li>To troubleshoot bugs and support requests</li>
        <li>To improve capture, annotation, and export workflows</li>
        <li>To comply with legal obligations when required</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>7. Your Rights</h2>
      <p>
        You may contact us to ask what support-related information we hold, or request deletion where
        applicable. You can also remove locally stored app data by deleting the app and related files
        on your device.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>8. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, contact
        <a href="mailto:vivyshot@vivy.company"> vivyshot@vivy.company</a>.
      </p>
    </section>
  </LegalPage>
</BaseLayout>
